# Basic Concentration Problems

1. The half-life of drug X is 10 hours. If the initial concentration is 100 mg/L, what is the concentration 3 hours later?

Assuming the drug is given as IV bolus and follows first order kinetics $C(t) = C_0 * e^{-k*t}$ and half life $t_{1/2} = 0.693 / k$



::: {#4 .cell execution_count=1}
``` {.julia .cell-code}
tₕ = 10
t = 3
C₀ = 100

k, k_lat = k_latex(tₕ)
_, ct_lat = ct_latex(C₀,k,t, "mg/L")

display(k_lat)
display(ct_lat)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display .cell-output-markdown}
$k = \frac{0.693}{t_{h}}$\begin{equation*}
k = \frac{0.693}{10} = 0.069\ hr^{-1}
\end{equation*}

:::

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display .cell-output-markdown}
$Time = 3\ hr$\begin{equation*}
C_t = 100 \cdot \mathscr{e}^{ - 0.069 \cdot 3} = 81.229\ mg/L
\end{equation*}

:::
:::





-------

