14. The concentration of drug X is 100 mg/L 0 hours postdose and 50 mg/L 8 hours postdose. What is the half-life of the drug? If the dose was 1000 mg what is the volume of distribution and the clearance?



::: {#30 .cell execution_count=1}
``` {.julia .cell-code}
C₀ = 100
t₀ = 0

Cₜ₂ = 50
t2 = 8

A = 1000
Cu = "mg/L"

tₕ, th_lat = th_latex(C₀,t₀,Cₜ₂,t2,Cu)
k, k_lat =  k_latex(tₕ)
vd, vd_lat = vd_latex(A, C₀, "mg", "L")
Cl, cl_lat = cl_latex(vd, k, "L")

display(th_lat)
display(k_lat)
display(vd_lat)
display(cl_lat)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display .cell-output-markdown}
$t_{1} = 0\ hr, \ $$t_{2} = 8\ hr, \ $\begin{equation*}
t_h = \frac{0.693 \cdot \left( 8 - 0 \right)}{\log\left( 100 \right) - \log\left( 50 \right)} = 7.998\ mg/L
\end{equation*}

:::

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display .cell-output-markdown}
$k = \frac{0.693}{t_{h}}$\begin{equation*}
k = \frac{0.693}{7.998} = 0.087\ hr^{-1}
\end{equation*}

:::

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display .cell-output-markdown}
$Amount = 1000\ mg$\begin{equation*}
V_{d} = \frac{1000}{100} = 10.0\ L
\end{equation*}

:::

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display .cell-output-markdown}
$Cl = V_{d} \cdot k$\begin{equation*}
Cl = 10 \cdot 0.087 = 0.866\ L/hr
\end{equation*}

:::
:::





