# AUC Problems

18. The AUC following a single 100 mg intravenous dose of drug Y was 10 mg*hr/L. The half-life was 2 hours. Calculate the clearance and volume of distribution.



::: {#38 .cell execution_count=1}
``` {.julia .cell-code}
A = 100
AUC = 10

tₕ = 2

k, k_lat = k_latex(tₕ)
Cl, cl_lat = cl_auc_latex(A, AUC, "L/hr")
vd, vd_lat = vd_cl_latex(Cl,k, "L")

display(cl_lat)
display(k_lat)
display(vd_lat)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display .cell-output-markdown}
$Cl = \frac{Dose}{AUC}$\begin{equation*}
Cl = \frac{100.0}{10.0} = 10.0\ L/hr
\end{equation*}

:::

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display .cell-output-markdown}
$k = \frac{0.693}{t_{h}}$\begin{equation*}
k = \frac{0.693}{2} = 0.346\ hr^{-1}
\end{equation*}

:::

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display .cell-output-markdown}
$V_{d} = \frac{Cl}{k}$\begin{equation*}
V_{d} = \frac{10.0}{0.346} = 28.86\ L
\end{equation*}

:::
:::





